answers.body_markdown:
The call to to `AVPacket.data()` returns a `BytePointer` which is a wrapper for the native C++ pointer. There is no capacity information associated with a pointer which means you need to set the capacity manually. You probably need something like:

    int packetSize = packet.size();
    ByteBuffer dataBuffer = packet.data().capacity(packetSize).asByteBuffer();

